    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I guess the idea was that an equation by itself (i.e. displayed with the `Math` class) should be left aligned, like any other output would be. Possibly it doesn't make sense for block equations in markdown. Can you see a way of making the CSS selector more specific so it would differentiate between those cases?"
